  "architectureOverview": "The artifact tree system is built on a hierarchical trie structure with three primary execution paths: propagation, filtering, and transformation. Propagation executes and emits artifact events. Filters process streams and emit filtered artifacts. Transformers execute operations and establish parent-child artifact relationships. All artifact emissions flow through the ArtifactEventListener, which triggers persistence via SaveGraphEventToGraphRepositoryListener. The system uses content-hash based deduplication at the node level and buffers orphan artifacts until their parents are established. Null outputs are handled gracefully throughout the execution pipeline.",
